                        },
                        "displayName": "Michael Milton",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Etc/UTC"
                    },
                    "body": "Well I want my approach to be totally compatible with classes I don't control, which is why I want to be able to register serializers rather than doing it all manually. For example, I could check if any given object has a `__dict__` and if so, convert to dict, otherwise pickle it. The `requests.Response` is something that I would like to be able to support, for example.",
